CommitDate: Sun Jul 12 13:44:10 2026 +0200

    docs: apply 4th Codex pass fixes to goal_actions spec
    
    Codex 4th pass verdict NOT-PLAN-READY, 2 holes verified against live code:
    
    - 2.2 disjoint-map-values claim REFUTED: send_mail's live row
      (intent_tags='notify,send') matches BOTH email:{send} and notify:{notify}
      despite the map values being disjoint. Replaced with the correct
      max-one-verb-per-LIVE-terminal invariant + a specificity-based
      disambiguation rule (rarer tag wins -> send_mail resolves to email).
      Test (h) is now RED-first, reproducing the double-match.
    
    - 2.8 'reuse the existing vocab-reject retry loop' REFUTED: that loop
      (_infer_capability_tags 545-568) runs pre-planner and only handles port
      tags; _select_chain swallows structured errors into a generic 'no healthy
      chain'. Added an explicit decode path (UnknownActionVerbError) + one-shot
      reinference on the planner-error path, with section-3 table rows + tests.
    
    2.6 start gate and 2.7 slug-scoped auth were Codex-CONFIRMED sound.
    Header status -> FOUR passes; next gate is a 5th pass on these two folds.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

