1. In `~/.hermes/cli-registry.db`, both `send` and `notify` occur on exactly one live capability—`send_mail`. Their rarity is therefore tied 1–1, so the specified “equal rarity is a hard error” rule cannot resolve `send_mail → email`. The stated count of three `notify` CLIs comes from this repo’s different `registry.db`, which contains those three rows but no `send_mail`; the spec combines distributions from two databases.

2. The formal invariant and test (h) remain incompatible with the preferred match-time fix. With `send_mail.intent_tags='notify,send'` unchanged, the stated raw-intersection expression still returns both `email` and `notify` after disambiguation. Test (h) can only become green by retagging or by redefining the invariant/test over the single resolved verb produced by the disambiguator.

